]]}}\n* {{small|\"[[The Shadow of Your Smile]]\" by [[Tony Bennett]]}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.awardsandshows.com/features/grammy-awards-1966-241.html|title=Grammy Awards Nominees 1966 - Grammy Award Winners 1966|last=|first=|date=|website=www.awardsandshows.com|access-date=April 26, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" align=\"center\"|[[Grammy Awards of 1967|1967]]\n| {{sortname|Frank|Sinatra}}<br />{{small|{{dot}}produced by [[Jimmy Bowen]]}}\n| {{sort|Strangers in the Night|\"[[Strangers in the Night]]\"}}\n|\n* {{small|\"[[Almost Persuaded (song)|Almost Persuaded]]\" by [[David Houston (singer)|David Houston]]}}\n* {{small|\"[[Monday, Monday]]\" by [[The Mamas & the Papas]]}}\n* {{small|\"[[What Now My Love (song)|What Now My Love]]\" by [[Herb Alpert]] and the Tijuana Brass}}\n* {{small|\"[[Winchester Cathedral (song)|Winchester Cathedral]]\" by [[The New Vaudeville Band]]}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"Grammy Awards 1967\">{{cite web|url=http://www.awardsandshows.com/features/grammy-awards-1967-214.html|title=Grammy Awards 1967|publisher=Awards & Shows}}{{Dead link|date=January 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> \n|-\n| scope=\"row\" align=\"center\"|[[Grammy Awards of 1968|1968]]\n| {{sort|Fifth Dimension, The|[[The 5th Dimension]]}}<br />{{small|{{dot}}produced by [[Johnny Rivers]] & Marc Gordon}}\n| {{sort|Up, Up and Away|\"[[Up, Up and Away (song)|Up, Up and Away]]\"}} *\n|\n* {{small|\"[[By the Time I Get to Phoenix]]\" by [[Glen Campbell]]}}\n* {{small|\"[[My Cup Runneth Over]]\" by [[Ed Ames]]}}\n* {{small|\"[[Ode to Billie Joe]]\" by [[Bobbie Gentry]]}}\n* {{small|\"[[Somethin' Stupid]]\" by [[Nancy Sinatra]] & [[Frank Sinatra]]}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.india-server.com/awards/features/grammy-awards-1968-218.html|title=Grammy Awards 1968|publisher=IndiaServer|access-date=December 10, 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110519012644/http://www.india-server.com/awards/features/grammy-awards-1968-218.html|archive-date=May 19, 2011|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" align=\"center\"|[[Grammy Awards of 1969|1969]]\n| {{sort|[Simon & Garfunkel|[[Simon & Garfunkel]]}}<br />{{small|{{dot}}produced by [[Art Garfunkel]], [[Paul Simon]] & [[Roy Halee]]}}\n| {{sort|Mrs. Robinson|\"[[Mrs. Robinson]]\"}}\n|\n* {{small|\"[[Harper Valley PTA]]\" by [[Jeannie C. Riley]]}}\n* {{small|\"[[Hey Jude]]\" by [[The Beatles]]}}\n* {{small|\"[[Honey (Bobby Goldsboro song)|Honey]]\" by [[Bobby Goldsboro]]}}\n* {{small|\"[[Wichita Lineman]]\" by [[Glen Campbell]]}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.awardsandshows.com/features/grammy-awards-1969-243.html|title=Grammy Awards Nominees 1969 - Grammy Award Winners 1969|last=|first=|date=|website=www.awardsandshows.com|access-date=April 26, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" align=\"center\"|[[Grammy Awards of 1970|1970]]\n| {{sort|Fifth Dimension, The|[[The 5th Dimension]]}}<br />{{small|{{dot}}produced by [[Bones Howe]]}}\n| {{sort|Aquarius|\"[[Aquarius/Let the Sunshine In]]\"}}\n|\n* {{small|\"[[A Boy Named Sue]]\" by [[Johnny Cash]]}}\n* {{small|\"[[Is That All There Is?]]\" by [[Peggy Lee]]}}\n* {{small|\"[[Love Theme from Romeo and Juliet]]\" by [[Henry Mancini]]}}\n* {{small|\"[[Spinning Wheel (song)|Spinning Wheel]]\" by [[Blood, Sweat & Tears]]}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.india-server.com/awards/features/grammy-awards-1970-219.html|title=Grammy Awards 1970|publisher=IndiaServer}}</ref>\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" align=\"center\"|[[Grammy Awards of 1971|1971]]\n| {{sort|[Simon & Garfunkel|[[Simon & Garfunkel]]}}<br />{{small|{{dot}}produced by [[Art Garfunkel]], [[Paul Simon]] & [[Roy Halee]]}}\n| {{sort|Bridge over Troubled Water|\"[[Bridge over Troubled Water (song)|Bridge over Troubled Water]]\"}} *\n|\n* {{small|\"[[(They Long to Be) Close to You]]\" by [[The Carpenters|Carpenters]]}}\n* {{small|\"[[Everything Is Beautiful]]\" by [[Ray Stevens]]}}\n* {{small|\"[[Fire and Rain (song)|Fire and Rain]]\" by [[James Taylor]]}}\n* {{small|\"[[Let It Be (Beatles song)|Let it Be]]\" by [[The Beatles]]}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.india-server.com/awards/features/grammy-awards-1971-220.html|title=Grammy Awards 1971|publisher=IndiaServer}}</ref>\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" align=\"center\"|[[Grammy Awards of 1972|1972]]\n| {{sortname|Carole|King}}<br />{{small|{{dot}}produced by [[Lou Adler]]}}\n| {{sort|It's Too Late|\"[[It's Too Late (Carole King song)|It's Too Late]]\"}}\n|\n* {{small|\"[[Joy to the World (Three Dog Night song)|Joy to the World]]\" by [[Three Dog Night]]}}\n* {{small|\"[[My Sweet Lord]]\" by [[George Harrison]]}}\n* {{small|\"[[Theme from Shaft|Theme from ''Shaft'']]\" by [[Isaac Hayes]]}}\n* {{small|\"[[You've Got a Friend]]\" by [[James Taylor]]}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.india-server.com/awards/features/grammy-awards-1972-221.html|title=Grammy Awards 1972|publisher=IndiaServer}}</ref>\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" align=\"center\"|[[Grammy Awards of 1973|1973]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"| {{sortname|Roberta|Flack}}<br />{{small|{{dot}}produced by [[Joel Dorn]]}}\n| {{sort|The First Time Ever I Saw Your Face|\"[[The First Time Ever I Saw Your Face]]\"}} *\n|\n* {{small|\"[[Alone Again (Naturally)]]\" by [[Gilbert O'Sullivan]]}}\n* {{small|\"[[American Pie (song)|American Pie]]\" by [[Don McLean]]}}\n* {{small|\"[[Song Sung Blue]]\" by [[Neil Diamond]]}}\n* {{small|\"[[Without You (Badfinger song)#Harry Nilsson version|Without You]]\" by [[Harry Nilsson|Nilsson]]}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.india-server.com/awards/features/grammy-awards-1973-222.html|title=Grammy Awards 1973|publisher=IndiaServer}}</ref>\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" align=\"center\"|[[Grammy Awards of 1974|1974]]\n| {{sort|Killing Me Softly with His Song|\"[[Killing Me Softly with His Song]]\"}} *\n|\n*