snews.com/news/winners-51st-grammy-awards/|title=Winners: 51st Grammy Awards|date=December 4, 2008|work=CBS News|accessdate=October 20, 2019}}</ref>\n|-style=\"background:#FAEB86;\" \n| \"[[Please Read the Letter]]\"\n| [[Robert Plant]] & [[Alison Krauss]]\n| [[T Bone Burnett]], producer; [[Mike Piersante]], engineer/mixer\n|-\n| \"[[Bleeding Love]]\"\n| [[Leona Lewis]]\n| [[Simon Cowell]], [[Clive Davis]] & [[Ryan Tedder]], producers; Craig Durrance, [[Phil Tan]] & [[Ryan Tedder]], engineers/mixers\n|-\n| \"[[Chasing Pavements]]\"\n| [[Adele]]\n| [[Eg White]], producer; [[Tom Elmhirst]] & [[Steven Price (composer)|Steve Price]], engineer/mixers\n|-\n| \"[[Paper Planes (M.I.A. song)|Paper Planes]]\"\n| [[M.I.A. (artist)|M.I.A.]]\n| [[Diplo]], producer; [[Switch (house DJ)|Switch]], engineer/mixer\n|-\n| \"[[Viva la Vida]]\"\n| [[Coldplay]]\n| [[Markus Dravs]], [[Brian Eno]] & [[Rik Simpson]], producers; [[Michael Brauer]] & [[Rik Simpson]], engineers/mixers\n|-\n|}\n\n===2010s===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#bebebe\"\n! width=\"5%\" | Year\n! width=\"15%\" | Record\n! width=\"15%\" | Artist(s)\n! width=\"65%\" | Production team\n|-\n|rowspan=\"6\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| [[52nd Annual Grammy Awards|2010]]<br /><ref name=Grammy2010>{{cite web|url=http://www2.grammy.com/grammy_awards/52nd_show/list.aspx#04 |title=The 52nd Annual Grammy Awards Nominees List |publisher=[[The Recording Academy]] |accessdate=October 18, 2019 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100618185140/http://www2.grammy.com/GRAMMY_Awards/52nd_show/list.aspx |archivedate=June 18, 2010 |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n|-style=\"background:#FAEB86;\" \n| \"[[Use Somebody]]\"\n| [[Kings of Leon]]\n| [[Jacquire King]] & [[Angelo Petraglia]], producers; [[Jacquire King]], engineer/mixer\n|-\n| \"[[Halo (Beyonc\u00e9 song)|Halo]]\"\n| [[Beyonc\u00e9]]\n| [[Beyonc\u00e9|Beyonc\u00e9 Knowles]] & [[Ryan Tedder]], producers; Jim Caruana, [[Spike Stent|Mark \"Spik