nees |archivedate=13 February 2017 }}</ref>\n|-style=\"background:#FAEB86;\" \n| \"[[Hello (Adele song)|Hello]]\"\n| [[Adele]]\n| [[Greg Kurstin]], producer; Julian Burg, [[Tom Elmhirst]], [[Greg Kurstin]], Liam Nolan & Alex Pasco, engineers/mixers; [[Tom Coyne (music engineer)|Tom Coyne]] & Randy Merrill, mastering engineers\n|-\n| \"[[Formation (song)|Formation]]\"\n| [[Beyonc\u00e9]]\n| [[Beyonc\u00e9|Beyonc\u00e9 Knowles]], [[Mike Will Made It]] & Pluss, producers; [[Jaycen Joshua]] & Stuart White, engineers/mixers; Dave Kutch, mastering engineer \n|-\n| \"[[7 Years (Lukas Graham song)|7 Years]]\"\n| [[Lukas Graham]]\n| [[Future Animals]] & Pilo, producers; Delbert Bowers, Sebastian Fogh, [[Stefan Forrest]] & David LaBrel, engineers/mixers; [[Tom Coyne (music engineer)|Tom Coyne]], mastering engineer\n|-\n| \"[[Stressed Out]]\"\n| [[Twenty One Pilots]]\n| [[Mike Elizondo]] & [[Tyler Joseph]], producers; [[Neal Avron]] & [[Adam Hawkins]], engineers/mixers; [[Chris Gehringer]], mastering engineer\n|-\n| \"[[Work (Rihanna song)|Work]]\"\n| [[Rihanna]] featuring [[Drake (musician)|Drake]]\n| [[Boi-1da]], producer; Noel \"Gadget\" Campbell, [[Kuk Harrell]], [[Manny Marroquin]], [[40 (record producer)|Noah \"40\" Shebib]] & Marcos Tovar, engineers/mixers; [[Chris Gehringer]], mastering engineer\n|-\n|rowspan=\"6\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| [[60th Annual Grammy Awards|2018]]<br /><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.grammy.com/grammys/news/2018-grammy-awards-complete-winners-list|title=Grammy Awards: Record of the Year 2017 |last=|first=|date=|work=[[The Recording Academy]]|access-date=October 18, 2019}}</ref>\n|-style=\"background:#FAEB86;\" \n| \"[[24K Magic (song)|24K Magic]]\"\n| [[Bruno Mars]]\n| [[The Smeezingtons|Shampoo Press & Curl]], producers; Serban Ghenea, John Hanes & [[Charles Moniz]], engineers/mixers; [[Tom Coyne (music engineer)|Tom Coyne]], mastering engineer\n|-\n| \"[[Despacito]]\"\n| [[Luis Fonsi]] & [[Daddy Yankee]] featuring [[Justin Bieber]]\n|